   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON EIGHTEEN THE EXERCISE OF OUR SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR GODLINESS Scripture Reading: 1 Tim 1:3-4; 3:15-16; 4:7-8; 6:11; 2 Tim 3:12, 5; 4:22; 2:22 OUTLINE God's economy 1 Tim 1:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The mystery of godliness 1 Tim 3:15-16: God manifested in the flesh.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The church of the living God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Exercising ourselves unto godliness 1 Tim 4:7-8: Bodily exercise profiting for a little.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Godliness being profitable for all things: Of the present life.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Of the coming life.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Pursuing godliness to be a man of God 1 Tim 6:11.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Living godly in Christ 2 Tim 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Having the power of godliness 2 Tim 3:5.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The Lord being with our spirit 2 Tim 4:22: Contacting the Lord by exercising our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Thus receiving grace.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Calling on the Lord 2 Tim 2:22: Out of a pure heart.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>With the Lord's callers.</S>
   </TEXT>
